---->Git:-
	Git is a Source Code Management(SCM) Tool.It is also called as Distributed Version Control System(DVCS).
	It is developed by Linus Torvald in 2005.

----> Installing Git on Linux:-
	sudo yum -y install git
		or
	sudo apt-get install git

----> To check the version of git installed:-
	git --version

----> Initialising a Local Git repository:-
	git init [directory_name]
		or
	git init (By default it will initalise the current directory as git repository).
	Note:- Directory is added with .git folder where all configuration file related to repo is available and it tracks
	and manage repository.

---->  To Configure or Add "username and useremail" for repository:-
	1) For a particular repository:-
		git config user.name "Username"
		git config user.email "username@xyz.com"

	2) For adding globally so that every repo should have same configuration for usetname and useremail:-
		git config --global user.name "Username"
		git config --global user.email "username@xyz.com"

----> To check the Configuration of git repo:-
	git config --list

----> To add local repo to central repo:-
	git remote add origin <centralgit url>

----> To check status of git repo:-
	git status

----> To add workspace data into staging area:-
	git add .
		or
	git add [file_name or directory_name]

----> To commit code in git repo:-
	git commit -m "commit message" .
		or
	git commit -m "coomit message" [file_name or directory_name]

----> To check log file or commit details:-
	git log

----> To show particular commit:-
	git show <commit ID>

----> To set branch name for repo:-
	git branch -M [branch_name]

----> To push local repo to centralised repo:-
	git push -u origin [branch_name]

----> To Pull centralised repo to local repo:-
	git pull -u origin [branch_name]

----> To learn about .gitignore:-
	If one want to ignore particular format of file one should add it in
	.gitignore file and then add it to staging area and commmit the change.
		git add .gitignore
		git commit -m "added gitignore file" .gitignore

----> To see n number of commits:-
	git log -n

----> To see commits in oneline:-
	git log --oneline

----> To see list of available Branches:-
	git branch
	Note:- * before name of branch will show that it is current working branch.

----> Create a new branch:-
	git branch [branch_name]

----> To switch to a particular branch:-
	git checkout <branch to be switched>

----> To delete a particular Branch:-
	git branch -d [branch_name]

----> To merge a branch:-
	git merge <branch_name>

----> To stash an item (Only applies to modifiedfile):-
	git stash

----> To see the list of item in stash:-
	git stash list

----> To apply stashed Items:-
	git stash apply stash@{0}

----> To clear the stash items:-
	git stash clear

----> To reset Staging Area:-
	git reset <filename>

----> To reset the change from both staging area and working directory at a time:-
	git reset --hard

----> To revert or undo an existing commit:-
	git revert <commit_ID>

----> To remove untracked file:-
	git clean -n (dry run)
		or
	git clean -f (forcefully)

----> To apply tag to a specific commit:-
	git tag -a <tagname> -m <message> <commit_ID>

----> To see the list of tags :-
	git tag

----> To see particular commit content by using tag:-
	git show <tag_name>

----> To delete a tag:-
	git tag -d <tag_name>

---->To clone a git repo:-
	git clone <url of centralised git repo>

